  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Louisiana Appleseed</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Funding from UUSC will allow Louisiana Appleseed to educate residents affected by the 2016 flooding about clear title and to work with direct legal service providers and pro bono attorneys to assist residents with the process.  Funding also will allow Louisiana Appleseed to continue much needed advocacy work in this area.  Most notably, we will be able to educate and encourage policy makers and legislators to adopt laws, rules and policies that will allow more residents to use the streamlined and less costly Heirship Affidavit process to properly and legally transfer title into the names of the proper heirs.  Allowing people to rebuild and return home after a disaster also helps proactively address blight and more broadly, revitalize whole neighborhoods more quickly.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">To coordinate and provide immediate support to legal aid services assisting flood victims in the twenty affected parishes in Louisiana, and to work with legal aid services to identify systemic issues for legislative advocacy</narrative>
  </description>
